tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  38,30,"And We gave unto David Solomon; how excellent a servant he was! He was a penitent."
  38,33,"Return them to me!' And he began to stroke their shanks and necks."
  38,39,"'This is Our gift; bestow or withhold without reckoning.'"
  38,40,"And he had a near place in Our presence and a fair resort."